olive oil
2 clove garlic
3 sachet peanut butter
4 tbs soy sauce
1 unit lime
2 tsp brown sugar
4 tbs hot water
1 packet beef strips
1 unit cucumber
1 unit carrot
1 unit fresh chilli
12 unit Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Crispy Shallots
4 tsp honey
1 unit cos lettuce

Finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). In a medium bowl, combine the honey, 1/2 the garlic and 2 1/2 tbs soy sauce. Add the beef strips and toss to coat. Set aside.

Juice the lime. In a small bowl, combine the lime juice, peanut butter, brown sugar, hot water, 1 1/2 tbs soy sauce and the remaining garlic. Add a drizzle of olive oil and mix well with a whisk or fork. TIP:  Taste the peanut butter sauce and add more brown sugar if you like!

Cut the cucumber into 0.5cm batons. Finely shred the cos lettuce. Thinly slice the long red chilli (if using). Grate the carrot (unpeeled).

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a high heat. Once hot, add 1/2 the beef and cook, tossing, for 1-2 minutes or until cooked through. Transfer to a plate. Repeat with the remaining beef strips.

Heat the mini flour tortillas in a sandwich press or on a plate in the microwave for 10 second bursts, or until warmed through.

Bring everything to the table. Build your own tacos by adding some cos lettuce, cucumber and carrot and topping it with some beef strips. Spoon the peanut sauce over the tacos. Garnish the adult portions with crispy shallots and long red chilli (if using).

TIP:  For kids, follow our serving suggestion in the main photo!